  <prompt>
    Compose a Phase B integration test exercising every Phase B deliverable end-to-end:

    (1) TL;DR rendering — invoke `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` against a test
        document; verify `tldr: string[]` renders as a Fluent v9 bulleted list (task 040).
    (2) Entities rendering — same invocation; verify `entities: { organizations, persons
        }` renders as labeled key-value blocks with nested bulleted lists (task 041).
    (3) Duplicate-fire elimination — type `/summarize` in chat; verify ONE rendered
        output (per task 042 CapabilityRouter dedup). Test BOTH natural-language
        ("summarize this document") and slash (`/summarize`) entry paths.
    (4) Matter-prefill regression — run end-to-end pre-fill on a test matter; verify
        wizard fields populate identically to BEFORE-task-034 baseline (NFR-07 binding).
    (5) Project-prefill regression — run end-to-end pre-fill on a test project; verify
        wizard fields populate identically to BEFORE-task-035 baseline (NFR-07 binding).
    (6) Backward compatibility — invoke an action whose row has NULL `sprk_outputschemajson`;
        verify widget falls back to string rendering (no regression on non-migrated
        actions).

    Each scenario produces evidence (screenshots, server logs, before/after diffs)
    stored under `notes/task-048-phase-b-integration-evidence.md`. Any failure requires
    diagnosis + fix BEFORE marking complete. This task gates task 049 (Phase B exit gate
    validation).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Integration tester comfortable composing end-to-end
    scenarios across BFF + frontend + Dataverse seed data. Familiar with R5 SC-18
    walkthrough methodology — the same disciplined evidence capture applies here.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Documented Phase B integration test report at
    `notes/task-048-phase-b-integration-evidence.md` covering all 6 scenarios above
    with evidence (screenshots, logs, before/after diffs). All 6 scenarios PASS. Phase B
    is provably exit-ready: schema-aware widget works (arrays + objects), dedup works
    (one render per intent), pre-fill regressions clean (NFR-07 honored), backward
    compatibility preserved.
  </goal>

