  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD
      📋 REASON: Integration test composition; tags include `integration-test`
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS: 8 steps; Step 9.5 quality gates SKIPPED per STANDARD rigor
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress + Confirm Prerequisites">
      Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 048 status 🔲; deps (042, 034, 035) complete. Read
      task 034 + 035 pre-fill regression test BEFORE baselines; confirm they exist.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Scenario 1: TL;DR Rendering">
      Open SpaarkeAi workspace shell against a test matter. Trigger
      `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` against a deterministic test document.
      Wait for `streaming_complete`. Capture screenshot of `tldr` field rendering.
      Verify: rendered DOM uses semantic `<ul>` with multiple `<li>` children; no raw
      JSON tokens visible; no console errors. Record in evidence notes.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Scenario 2: Entities Rendering">
      Same invocation, but inspect `entities` field. Verify: rendered DOM uses labeled
      sections (Organizations, Persons) with nested bulleted lists; no raw JSON object
      literal visible. Record screenshot + evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Scenario 3: Duplicate-Fire Elimination">
      In chat, type `/summarize` (slash form). Verify: ONE rendered output. Inspect
      server logs to confirm: ONE LLM call, ONE playbook execution, ONE DeliverOutput,
      ONE render. Repeat for natural-language form ("summarize this document"). Verify
      same single-render behavior. Record server log excerpts (tool names + decisions
      + timestamps ONLY per ADR-015 — no user message text).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Scenario 4: Matter Pre-Fill Regression">
      Run end-to-end pre-fill on the SAME test matter document used in task 034 BEFORE
      baseline. Capture AFTER values: wizard fields populated + per-field values +
      end-to-end latency. Diff against task 034 AFTER baseline (which was already
      verified at task-034 close). Verify ZERO drift since task 034 close. Record
      evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Scenario 5: Project Pre-Fill Regression">
      Run end-to-end pre-fill on the SAME test project document used in task 035
      BEFORE baseline. Capture AFTER values. Diff against task 035 AFTER baseline.
      Verify ZERO drift. Record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Scenario 6: Backward Compatibility">
      Invoke an action whose row has NULL `sprk_outputschemajson` (e.g., a not-yet-migrated
      action — verify via query). Confirm widget renders as today (string formatting).
      No crash; no error. Record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Compose Phase B Integration Report + Complete">
      Compose `notes/task-048-phase-b-integration-evidence.md`: pass/fail per scenario
      with evidence references. Confirm BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no BFF code
      changed by this task). If any scenario failed, document the issue + STOP for
      escalation. Otherwise: update TASK-INDEX.md: 048 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md`.
      Report completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
